Class JavaParser.WhitespaceToken

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.pump.io.Token
      • com.pump.io.java.JavaParser.WhitespaceToken
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<Token>
    Enclosing class:
    JavaParser

    public static class JavaParser.WhitespaceToken
extends Token
    This token is used to represent a consecutive series of whitespace.

    Note this is the only token where the line number attribute is misleading. This token may include several line returns, so the line number this ends on may not be the line number this starts on.

    • Method Detail

      • split

        public JavaParser.WhitespaceToken[] split(char... markers)
        Split this token into a series of tokens that end in the character(s) provided. For example, if this token represents: "\\t\\t\\n\\t" and you split using the "\\n" char, then this will return two tokens: "\\t\\t\\n" and "\\t"
        Parameters:
        markers - characters that mark where to break to start a new token.
        Returns:
        a series of tokens that are parts of this token.
